entry.title: What Is Juneteenth? And How Did It Become a Federal Holiday?
entry.content: The celebration commemorates the day when the last enslaved African-Americans were informed they were free.

entry.title: Ukraine's Offensive Is a Battle of Readiness
entry.content: The coming battles with Russian troops ultimately will boil down to which side has better prepared and strengthened over recent months.

entry.title: Homeless Numbers Rise in U.S. Cities
entry.content: A Wall Street Journal review of data from around the nation finds sharper increases than in recent years as pandemic-era protections end and housing costs climb.
